.TH "datagram_poll" 9 "datagram_poll" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
datagram_poll \- generic datagram poll
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "__poll_t" datagram_poll
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "poll_table *wait "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
file struct
.IP "sock" 12
socket
.IP "wait" 12
poll table

Datagram poll: Again totally generic. This also handles
sequenced packet sockets providing the socket receive queue
is only ever holding data ready to receive.
.SH "NOTE"
when you *don't* use this routine for this protocol,
and you use a different write policy from \fBsock_writeable\fP
then please supply your own write_space callback.
